  "explanation": [
    {
      "heading": "WebSocket: Full-Duplex Channel",
      "body": "HTTP is request-response — client must ask to receive data.\n\nWebSocket is a **persistent TCP connection**: both sides can send at any time. Perfect for chat — messages arrive instantly without polling.",
      "appearsAtStep": 0
    },
    {
      "heading": "Message Queue: The Reliability Layer",
      "body": "Messages go through a Message Queue (Kafka, RabbitMQ) before delivery.\n\nThis decouples senders from receivers and guarantees **at-least-once delivery**.\n\nIf the destination WebSocket server is down, the queue retains the message.",
      "appearsAtStep": 1
    },
    {
      "heading": "Offline Delivery: Queue + Push",
      "body": "When recipient is offline:\n1. Message stored in DB\n2. Push notification sent via APNS/FCM\n3. On reconnect, client fetches missed messages from DB (via cursor-based pagination)\n\nThis is **store-and-forward** — the same model used by email.",
      "appearsAtStep": 4
    },
    {
      "heading": "Reconnect: Drain the Queue",
      "body": "On reconnect, the client sends its **last seen message ID**.\n\nThe server fetches all messages after that ID from the DB and pushes them in order.\n\nThis ensures no message is skipped even if the client was offline for days.",
      "appearsAtStep": 5
    }
  ],

  "popups": [
    {
      "id": "pop-ws-vs-polling",
      "attachTo": "chat-system",
      "text": "Long Polling: client re-requests every N seconds — 100× more overhead",
      "showAtStep": 0,
      "hideAtStep": 1,
      "style": "info",
      "anchor": { "x": 50, "y": 85 }
    },
    {
      "id": "pop-offline-queue",
      "attachTo": "chat-system",
